Pass C compiler flags through to assembly sources in cgo mode.

The internal patch relies on assembler invocations seeing the same include and define flags that cgo-generated C compilation already sees. Without that, mixed cgo and assembly targets can compile the C side correctly while the assembly side misses generated headers or macro definitions.

This port keeps the change isolated to the assembly source branch in cgo2 so the rest of the cgo builder flow stays unchanged.

